subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
Stridulatory file on underside of left tegmen with about 10 undeveloped teeth in the basal part, and 36 normal teeth in the other part (
Figure 3E
). Tenth abdominal tergum with each lateral lobe short and forcipate, the median process large, elevated, and with its posterior margin approximating the apices of the lateral lobes (
Figure 7A, B
). Epiproct smaller, slightly wider than long, dorsally concave entad, without black bristles in the ventral surface, and bearing a pair of relatively short spine-like lateral processes at apex, which are projected dorsad, notch between trapezoid (
Figure 7C, D
). Male subgenital plate with apical fourth incised, and the forked processes gently recurved (
Figure 7E
).
